---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Why Life Momentum Score measures net momentum instead of streaks — and the philosophy behind delayed score reveals."
>
  <article class="container-page py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
        Momentum, not streaks.
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-10">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">The idea</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Most habit trackers celebrate streaks and completion percentages. They tell you what you
            did well and quietly ignore everything working against you. The result is a flattering,
            incomplete picture.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Life Momentum Score takes a different stance. It treats your week as a single ledger:
            positive habits add momentum, negative habits subtract it, and the score you see is the
            honest net effect. You might log five workouts and still end the week in the negative —
            and that is exactly the kind of insight a streak counter will never give you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Why delayed reveals</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Checking a number every day turns reflection into a reflex. You start optimizing for the
            score instead of understanding your behavior. Weekly and Monthly reveal modes hide the
            number until the period ends, so you log honestly in the moment and confront the result
            with fresh eyes.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="mt-5 border-l-2 border-hairline-strong pl-4 text-base italic text-body">
            “Delayed score reveals help reduce daily bias and encourage more honest self-reflection.”
          </blockquote>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Private by design</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            This is version one. There are no accounts, no logins, and no servers. Every habit and
            entry is stored in your browser using localStorage, which means your data never leaves
            your device and the app keeps working after every refresh. Future versions may add
            optional cloud sync — but the default will always respect your privacy.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
        <a href="/dashboard" class="btn btn-primary inline-flex">Start Tracking</a>
        <a href="/features" class="btn btn-secondary inline-flex">Explore features</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
